
Video via http://www.ted.com/talks/view/id/944


=Description=

"In the words of Robert F. Kennedy, why does Gross National Product "measure everything [...] except that which makes life worthwhile"? What we really want are happiness and health, but we have the perception that those things can be measured on an economic scale. If happiness is what we want most, why aren't we measuring it directly?

Good news: statistician Nic Marks does just that. Watch as Marks explains the Happy Planet Index, his alternative to GDP, and what it tells us about which countries are really the happiest."
(http://www.yesmagazine.org/happiness/the-happy-planet-index)


